    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.44-44a_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection
                    45</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">44</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="italics">Yankton</hi> <hi rend="caps">COLLEGE</hi> Yankton, South Dakota
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italics">75<hi rend="underline">th Anniversary</hi> Year</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">OFFICE OF THE PRESIDENT</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 22, 1958</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>My husband a<del><unclear>d</unclear></del><add>n</add>d I wish to express our deep sympathy to you at this time of your sorrow. While we know you only through your works and distinguished reputation, we have developed a special feeling for you as we look forward to having you on our campus and as a guest at our Fine Arts Conference. We think with pleasure of the opportunity to become acquainted, and hope you will find your experience here a rewarding one.</p>
                
                <p>We admire your courage and kindness in responding to our request at a time when your personal life was all absorbing. Indeed you are remembered in our prayers.
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.44-44a_0002"/>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">44a</fw>
                
                    It is unusual that I, the wife of the president should be chairman of our Fine Arts Conference Committee, But the faculty elected me (I guess they thought I had more time than they) and I am so interested in this program, inaugurated last year. It is unique in the state, in including a "symposium" of arts in our conference We are receiving a very enouraging response and feel it is very worthwhile.</p>
                
                <p>We shall send you a complete program next week. Your picture didn't arrive in time to be included on the printed folder, but we shall use it widely in the state in newspaper coverage.</p>
                
                <p>Thank you for your splendid cooperation.</p>
                
                <p>We shall thank of you often these days and wish for you strength and faith in your hours of need.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely Yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Martha D. Rondileau</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
